01:46:25.025 --> 01:46:27.357
I'm gone!
Give me my paper route money.

01:46:27.594 --> 01:46:30.062
- That money is gone with the wind.
- No!

01:46:30.230 --> 01:46:31.458
I spent it.

01:46:31.798 --> 01:46:33.197
For things we needed!

01:46:33.366 --> 01:46:35.357
It's gone! Poof!

01:46:35.535 --> 01:46:38.936
Know something? It's not
that you're disappointing.

01:46:39.139 --> 01:46:44.543
- You're consistently disappointing.
- Fancy talk. Fancy talk for a whore.

01:46:44.711 --> 01:46:47.908
Yeah, I know a thing or two
about a thing or two.

01:46:48.081 --> 01:46:51.414
I got friends in this town
and they tell me things.

01:46:51.584 --> 01:46:55.782
I heard a guy at campaign headquarters
got you a job in Washington, D.C.

01:46:55.955 --> 01:46:58.924
You're gonna run off with him,
right, whore?

01:46:59.092 --> 01:47:03.392
- You're pathetic.
- Miss Whore. Liar! Whore! You know it.

01:47:03.697 --> 01:47:05.187
Mom, you can leave too.

01:47:05.365 --> 01:47:08.698
I'm leaving.
You don't have to stay for this shit!

01:47:09.769 --> 01:47:11.168
- I don't, do I?
- No.

01:47:11.337 --> 01:47:15.103
- Liar! Whore!
- I could leave with you, couldn't I?

01:47:15.275 --> 01:47:16.537
Yes, you could.

01:47:16.710 --> 01:47:19.679
- I could walk right out, couldn't I?
- Yes.

01:47:19.846 --> 01:47:21.814
- What?
- I'm leaving you, Dwight.

01:47:21.981 --> 01:47:25.348
- No. No, you're not. What about me?
- I'm leaving.

01:47:25.518 --> 01:47:27.884
- What about me?
- I'm leaving you.

01:47:28.188 --> 01:47:30.383
Why stay? You don't even like me.

01:47:30.590 --> 01:47:33.423
No, you're not leaving.
You're not leaving.

01:47:33.593 --> 01:47:35.823
Keep away from us.

01:47:37.030 --> 01:47:40.329
You always sided against me,
thought you were better.

01:47:40.500 --> 01:47:44.459
I tried. I did the best I could.
What about me?

01:47:44.671 --> 01:47:48.607
What am I supposed to do?
Crawl off in some ditch and die?

01:47:48.775 --> 01:47:50.936
What about me?

01:47:55.582 --> 01:47:59.780
What about me? What about me?

01:48:00.386 --> 01:48:05.722
When is it ever Dwight's turn
for some consideration? What about me?

01:48:08.495 --> 01:48:12.454
I'll tell you one thing,
you'll remember me!

01:48:12.665 --> 01:48:15.031
- <i>It was as easy as that.</i>
- You'll remember me!

01:48:15.201 --> 01:48:17.795
<i>We just picked up and left.</i>

01:48:18.471 --> 01:48:23.135
<i>You can dream of a moment for years and</i>
<i>still somehow miss it when it comes.</i>

01:48:23.309 --> 01:48:28.303
<i>You've got to reach through the flames</i>
<i>and take it or lose it forever.</i>

01:48:28.481 --> 01:48:30.779
<i>I took it. So did my mother.</i>

01:48:31.551 --> 01:48:33.951
<i>We never looked back.</i>

01:48:43.329 --> 01:48:46.093
I borrowed money
from everybody we know.

01:48:46.266 --> 01:48:49.531
- So here's the extra $200 for tuition.
- Thanks.

01:48:49.702 --> 01:48:54.071
There's another 50 there, get
yourself a blazer or something, okay?

01:48:54.240 --> 01:48:55.730
Okay.

01:48:58.144 --> 01:48:59.771
Well...

01:49:01.080 --> 01:49:03.605
You're sure you're gonna be all right?

01:49:03.783 --> 01:49:08.447
Yeah, Mom, my bus comes in two hours.
I'll be fine.

01:49:15.228 --> 01:49:18.254
I'm going to miss you so much.

01:49:22.635 --> 01:49:24.933
Get on the bus, Mom.

01:49:31.744 --> 01:49:33.109
I love you.

01:49:36.249 --> 01:49:40.276
I know that, Mom.
I've always known that.

01:49:42.322 --> 01:49:44.153
All aboard.

01:49:49.629 --> 01:49:51.221
- Bye, honey.
- Bye.

01:50:03.076 --> 01:50:05.067
<i>I love you.</i>

